n<li>multiple</li>\n<li>name</li>\n<li>required</li>\n<li>size</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It is also possible to define groups of related options from a drop-down list within a <code>select</code> element.</p>\n<p>This is done by adding an <code>&#x3C;optgroup></code> attribute, like so:</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;select>\n  &#x3C;optgroup label="Fav Fruit">\n   &#x3C;option\n    value="apple">Apples\n    &#x3C;/option>\n   &#x3C;option\n    value="banana">Bananas\n   &#x3C;/option>\n   &#x3C;option\n    value="orange">Oranges\n   &#x3C;/option>\n  &#x3C;/optgroup\n  &#x3C;optgroup label="Fav Veggie">\n   &#x3C;option\n    value="carrot">Carrots\n   &#x3C;/option>\n   &#x3C;option\n    value="cucumber">Cucumbers\n   &#x3C;/option>\n   &#x3C;option\n    value="onion">Onions\n   &#x3C;/option>\n  &#x3C;/optgroup\n&#x3C;/select>\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="width:100%" viewBox="0 0 320 178"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="178" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><path fill="#3B99FC" stroke="#3497FF" d="M71 37.11593V21h11.07254c1.5431 1.05927 2.31463 2.59597 2.31463 4.6101 0 1.0728.36942 9.10886-1.15003 10.46117-1.52922 1.361-5.60826 1.70921-12.23714 1.04466z"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="11.5"><tspan x="28" y="33">Apples </tspan></text><rect width="64" height="17" x="20.5" y="20.5" stroke="#D9D9D9" rx="4"/><path stroke="#FFF" stroke-linecap="square" d="M75.375 26.625l2.25-2.25m-.25 0l2.25 2.25M75.5 30l2.25 2.25m2-2.25l-2.25 2.25"/><g transform="translate(27 34)"><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="11.5"><tspan x="3" y="10">Red</tspan></text><rect width="97" height="122" x=".5" y="1.5" fill="#F9FBFB" stroke="#D2D2D2" rx="4"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="11.5"><tspan x="21" y="18">Fav Fruit</tspan></text><path fill="#479AFE" d="M1 38h96v16H1z"/><text fill="#FFF" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="11.5"><tspan x="36